  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat and add ground mustard and cumin; toast for 1-2 minutes until fragrant, creating a bhuna.",
    "Add chopped onion, diced carrot, and celery to the pot; sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in minced garlic, smoked paprika, thyme, and bay leaf, cooking for another minute to bloom the spices.",
    "Pour in water, white wine, and fish stock, bringing the mixture to a gentle boil.",
    "Add cod cubes to the pot and reduce heat; simmer gently for 8-10 minutes until the fish is opaque and cooked through.",
    "Decrease heat and stir in heavy cream, letting the stew thicken slightly, about 2 minutes.",
    "Season with salt, pepper, lemon juice, and chopped dill; adjust seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot, spooning the silky broth over the cod, with a splash of extra dill if desired."
  ],
